System Engineer Core Banking at Knab 
Build, improve, scale! 
Knabâ€¯was founded in 2012 because we wanted to do things differently. Simpler, smarter and more advantageous for our customers. Because we believe we can help everyone maximize their financial affairs. "Feel at ease when it comes to your finances. Every day." By combining smart technical solutions with a healthy dose of human intelligence, we create financial services that really meet your needs. Add to that some of the sublime personal service from our employees and you end up with something that's truly unique to the world of finance. From banking to insurances, we've got your back!â€¯ 
All our colleagues have one thing in common: we each try to help customers maximize their money matters seamlessly and proactively. We're open minded, positive and committed to our customers. So, you gain control over your financial affairs 
In a nutshellâ€¯ 
You will be optimising our AWS Cloud environment for the core of our bank. You enjoy finding and implementing the best solutions (sometimes in consultation with suppliers) within our core bank platform. 
You are the enabler for the team on the whole software development lifecycle of the core banking systems, you focus on AWS keep our systems up-to-date, secure, and fast, to ensure Knab is in control. In your role you support the team in terms of controlling pipelines, releases. You are responsible for cloud infrastructure of the team, you coach other software engineers on DevOps principals, like infrastructure as code, yaml, pipelines etc. Operationally you are responsible for controlled release management, monitoring, and alerting (for example on infrastructure, networking, security) the team. 
The Team 
You are part of one of our multidisciplinary Agile teams within the IT Foundation value stream. The team focusses on developing and maintaining the proposition and the underlying infrastructure (private and public Cloud, CI/CD and monitoring).â€¯ 
A value stream within Knab contains multiple Agile teams focusing on the same customer proposition or service and are responsible for the product to be delivered. Within one of the value streams, you report to the IT Chapter Lead. By organizing this way we achieve more focus and a higher speed of delivery. 
Your Profile 
High quality is an important factor in your daily job; 
You are able to stay focused; 
You are an excellent team player; 
You have excellent communication skills; 
You understand what needs to be done to automate operations. 

Skills and knowledge we would love to see 
There is not a set route to become a great System Engineer at Knab, but to be successful in this role, this is the profile we have in mind:â€¯â€¯ 
Demonstrable experience as a System Engineer or Cloud engineer, with good knowledge of Amazon Web Services (at least 3 years hands on experience). ;
You have experiences with or are not afraid to set up and maintain a wide spectrum of IaaS and PaaS services. For example, networking (VPC, Cloudfront, Route 53, ELB) Compute (EC2, ECS, Lambda), Database/Storage/Cache (RDS, S3, ElastiCache), Monitoring & Alerting (like NewRelic, Datadog, Dynatrace) Others (System Manager, KMS, CloudWatch);
You have very good experience writing infrastructure as a code with Terraform, Infrastructure as Code and Configuration Management;
Experience with Azure DevOps (pipeline configuration);
Experience in scripting (Python, Powershell, HCL/JSON);
Experience with Containerization / Microservices (for example running applications services in AWS ECS or Kubernetes).

Work with us! 
If you come to work with us, Knab will become a significant part of your life. Therefore, we make sure the ambiance is just as exciting as your job. Check the benefits here! 
We don't collaborate with third parties to fulfill this role, nor are we open to freelance or contractors.
